🚀 AWS Free Tier Account Setup Guide
📌 Overview

This guide explains how to create an AWS Free Tier account step by step.
Perfect for students, developers, and beginners exploring cloud computing.

🧰 Prerequisites
📧 Valid email address
📱 Mobile phone number
💳 Credit/Debit card (for verification)
🌐 Internet connection
🗺️ Setup Workflow
flowchart TD
    A[Open AWS Free Tier Page] --> B[Enter Account Details]
    B --> C[Select Account Type]
    C --> D[Add Payment Method]
    D --> E[Verify Identity]
    E --> F[Choose Support Plan]
    F --> G[Account Activated]
    G --> H[Login to AWS Console]
🧾 Step-by-Step Procedure
1️⃣ Open AWS Free Tier Page

🔗 https://aws.amazon.com/free/
Click on Create a Free Account

2️⃣ Enter Account Details
Email address
Password
AWS account name
3️⃣ Select Account Type
👤 Personal (recommended)
🏢 Professional

Fill in:

Full name
Address
Phone number
4️⃣ Add Payment Method
💳 Enter card details
🔄 Small temporary charge may apply (refundable)
5️⃣ Verify Identity
📱 Enter phone number
🔐 Receive OTP (SMS/Call)
✅ Enter verification code
6️⃣ Choose Support Plan
🆓 Select Basic Support (Free)
7️⃣ Complete Registration
⏳ Wait for activation (few minutes)
🔐 Access AWS Console

🔗 https://console.aws.amazon.com/

Login using your credentials.

💡 Important Notes
⚠️ Free Tier has usage limits
📊 Monitor via AWS Billing Dashboard
🔔 Enable billing alerts
🛡️ Security Best Practices
🔒 Enable MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication)
👥 Create IAM user (avoid using root account)
💰 Configure budget alerts
